<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 15 at 5:54PM EDT until June 15 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 PM EDT
FOR CENTRAL CLAY COUNTY...
At 553 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hayesville,
moving northwest at 5 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Hayesville and Tusquitee.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
